Gwen sat at the back of the RV, reading more about the lost Keystone of Bezel before joining up with the others at the magic show. Her attention was caught on a particular site that mentioned a rumored way to destroy the Keystone. \par
"Destroy it?! Heck, no! But..." She turned her wrist, where the gauntlet holding the Keystone was, over, thinking hard, "It might just end up like the cemetary again. Wouldn't want anyone bad getting this. Hahhhh, alright, what the spell?" \par
She scrawled the magic words on a torn notebook scrap. "Hope I'll \b\i never\b0  \i0 need this," she said, tucking the piece into her pocket.\par
\par
Hours later, the Tennysons gazed up at the tower where Hex and Charmcaster were trying to restore the destroyed Charms of Bezel. Lucky Girl tightly clenched her fist, angry that she let the Keystone get swiped and hesitant about destroying another powerful artifact, but also determined not to let the magical duo capture such dangerous power for themselves. \par
So she readied herself, reciting the spell again from memory - she had made sure to do so on the ride here.\par
\par
After tussling with the two evil magicians, Charmcaster backstabbed Hex and was alone on the roof, about to receive the restore Charms. \par
Landing behind her was Lucky Girl, "I'm not going to let you get your way!" She yelled.\par
"Feh, as if \i you \i0 can do anything, anymore." Was the calm reply, Charmcaster turning her back to the ceremony above.\par
The wind swirled around the micro solar system of the Keystone, bursting with energy, orbited by the now restored and glowing Charms.\par
A deep sigh came from the masked youngster, who then yelled out the spell.\par
Immediately the air felt...distorted. The wind slowed and stopped. No magical crackles of lightning erupted from the Keystone. And the Charms stopped spinning, instead they shook, violently before blasting out into five directions. Then the Keystone itself turned dark, changing into a ball of void shadow and pulling in all the magical energy in the vicinity. \par
"Wha-what have you done?!" Charmcaster yelled as she felt her magic force drain from her body, losing consciousness. The magic flowed out of Hex, and even his staff. \par
"This is...not what I expected. Wait..." At that moment, the shadowy Keystone shot itself straight at Gwen, who lifted up an arm in a last ditch attempt to protect herself before collapsing on the roof.\par
\par
When she opened her eyes, she was back in the Rust Bucket, laying on the rear couch. \par
"What...happened?" \par
Ben was close-by and crouched up, "You fell or something while Grandpa and I were dealing with that falling coaster. We just found you out on the ground. We didn't know what happened and so we were rushing to the hospital!"\par
Max spoke up from behind the wheel, "Oh, thank goodness! Gwen, how are you? Don't worry, we're almost at the hospital!"\par
She struggled to sit up, "Urghh, I feel like...something hit me..." She swayed a little before falling back onto the couch.\par
"Woah, careful, we don't you passing out on us again!" Ben walked up to her, ready to catch her should she fall onto the floor.\par
"So, what about Hex and Charmcaster?" She said between deep breathes.\par
"Knocked out as well. What happened? The Keystone was gone when we got there and all three of you were out."\par
Gwen saw slices of memory return to her, "I'll tell you once we're done at the hospital. Everything's super hazy now."\par
Her cousin nodded, "You should probably slip on a sweater or something over that costume before we reach the hospital."\par
"Yeah, pass we a jacket?"\par
\par
\par
A few hours later, Gwen was admitted as having experienced total exhaustion, having completely passed out waiting for a doctor, and so was left to rest in a room for the night. \par
Max and Ben made themselves comfortable in a couple of chairs, watching over her the whole time.\par
The next morning she woke up with heavy eyelids. Her relatives were hunched over in their chairs - next to each other bedside to her.\par
Every part of her body felt done, like she had spent the whole day running, lifting, swimming and jumping without a break. Nothing was responding to her desires to move. All she could do was groan and look left to right. \par
"What's going on...? Why can't I move...? Ben, Grandpa..." She felt exhausted, even holding her eyes this open tired her out and soon, she fell asleep again. \par
\par
\par
\par
"...and we're not exactly sure what could be causing this."\par
"Hm. Okay."\par
She opened her eyes again to two figures talking above her bed. One was Grandpa Max, and the other...probably a doctor, she thought. She also noticed Ben, hovering by her side, with clear worry on his face.\par
"But that doesn't mean that it's something catastrophic. Again, it could simply be heat-induced exhaustion. Happens more often around these parts than you'd--"\par
Suddenly she felt the urge to get up, her body finally answering her request.\par
"Hey! She's awake!"\par
The three moved in closer to her, watching her closely.\par
Gwen yawned, stretching her arms out and sat up. "Hey. How's everyone doing?" She said rubbing her eye.\par
"Don't 'Hey' us! We thought you were never gonna wake!" Ben yelled, throwing his arms up.\par
"What?" Gwen replied.\par
Max filled her in, "You were asleep for a week. You didn't move or anything."\par
"What!?" Gwen replied, this time loudly.\par
The doctor stepped in, "Yes. We were all quite a bit worried, especially your cousin and grandfather here." She leaned in, looking over the ten year-old. "But, you look much healthier now. More energetic."\par
"Yep! Definitely feel \b\i alot\i0  \b0 more energetic now!"\par
"Well that's good." The doctor said, standing up and pulling out a notepad, "Perhaps we can send you home tomorrow, after a few tests."\par
"That would be great." Max said with a sigh of relief. "Thanks doc."\par
She smiled on her way out, "I'll call a nurse to give her a proper checkup."\par
Ben slumped back onto his chair, placed above her right shoulder, "You have \b\i no idea\b0\i0  how much we thought it was some weird-magic-curse that those two creeps mighta put on you."\par
"Ben's right, ha ha! We weren't sure whether it was something medical or magical." Max sat down on her bed, smiling non-stop.\par
"Sorry I worried you two. But I am a lot better now."\par
"Yeah, we can tell." Ben said, "You didn't even move that much to breathe! Doc said it was like you were in a coma, but without being in one."\par
"Woah, that sounds scary."\par
"It was." Her grandfather momentarily dropped his smile before reassuming his happy face.\par
"So..." Ben started, "Do you remember now what happened on the roof?"\par
She sighed, leaning back into her pillow, "Yeah it--"\par
A knocking on the door interrupted them as a nurse came in to give Gwen a checkup.\par
Max stood up and grabbed Ben, "We'll go down to the mess hall and grab ya some food. We've been in this room all day, it's nearly supper time!"\par
"Alright, but hurry back!" She said, waving around the nurse who are busy checking her fluid levels.\par
\par
